The Duke of Sussex makes a slew of bombshell claims and revelations in the book. These include an allegation his brother Prince William physically attacked him; that the Prince of Wales called Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, "difficult" and "rude" as well as King Charles pleading with his sons to stop their fight after Prince Philip's funeral at Windsor. Harry also reveals he killed 25 people during his tours of Afghanistan and addresses longstanding rumours about Major James Hewitt and his mother, Princess Diana. Spare includes details of the Duke's loss of virginity to an older woman in a field behind a very busy pub and his cocaine use. THIS LIVE BLOG HAS NOW ENDED